{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nCollapse the agent's monitoring to ONE call returning ONE typed outcome, so agents never correlate votes/labels/status ‚Äî and the \"both votes green but conflicts\" trap is handled inside the tool, not by every session.\n\n## What\nA project command (project CLI/script, NOT `rebar` core; may `import rebar` only for ticket ops) that requests a land and returns one typed terminal outcome + distinct exit code. Blocking `--wait` + single-shot `land-status`.\n\n## Dependencies\nDepends on **S1** (the `Autosubmit` label ‚Äî `land` sets it) and **S3** (the recorded outcome ‚Äî the authoritative source this command reads before falling back to native votes).\n\n## Scope\nThe agent-facing command + the outcome enum contract. Lives in project tooling, not `src/rebar`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `land <change> --wait` sets `Autosubmit`, blocks until terminal, returns one typed outcome as JSON + a **distinct exit code per outcome** per this table: `0 merged`, `1 needs_rebase`, `2 ci_failed`, `3 review_failed`, `124 timed_out`, any other failure ‚Üí `error` (nonzero, distinct from the above).\n- [ ] `land-status <change>` single-shot variant returns the same enum **plus a non-terminal `pending`** value while the bot is still driving (it does NOT set `Autosubmit` ‚Äî that is `land`'s job; this resolves the fire-and-forget-then-check-back flow: run `land <change>` once, poll `land-status` which returns `pending` until terminal).\n- [ ] **`--wait` termination/timeout:** poll `GET /changes/{id}` every 30s; detect terminal status (MERGED / ABANDONED / a failing label); overall timeout 30 min ‚Üí `timed_out` (exit `124`); transport errors are retried (bounded) before surfacing `error`.\n- [ ] **Fallback precedence** for deriving the outcome: (1) the bot's recorded outcome (S3) wins if present; else derive from native Gerrit state ‚Äî `Verified -1` ‚Üí `ci_failed`, `LLM-Review -1` ‚Üí `review_failed`, MERGED ‚Üí `merged`; if both `-1` are present with no bot record, `ci_failed` wins.\n- [ ] Command lives in PROJECT tooling (repo CLI/script), NOT `rebar` core; may `import rebar` only for ticket ops (e.g. close the ticket on merge). No Gerrit-specific landing logic in `src/rebar`.\n- [ ] The outcome enum is documented as a **stable, versioned contract** at `docs/land-contract.md` ‚Äî listing the enum values, the exit-code table, and a `contract-version`; `land --help` cites it and ADR-0042 references it. Agents depend only on this contract."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783725982275610001,"uuid":"0534df58-f178-49b7-83ef-ee0cc111aa53"}